J/A+A/468/1115     Thorium and argon lines in the visible   (Lovis+, 2007)
================================================================================
A new list of thorium and argon spectral lines in the visible.
    Lovis C., Pepe F.
   <Astron. Astrophys. 468, 1115 (2007)>
   =2007A&A...468.1115L
================================================================================
ADC_Keywords: Atomic physics ; Spectroscopy
Keywords: atomic data - techniques: spectroscopic - atlases - catalogs

Abstract:
    We present a new list of thorium and argon emission lines in the
    visible obtained by analyzing high-resolution (R=110000) spectra
    of a ThAr hollow cathode lamp. The aim of this new line list is to
    allow significant improvements in the quality of wavelength
    calibration for medium- to high-resolution astronomical spectrographs.

    We use a series of ThAr lamp exposures obtained with the HARPS
    instrument (High Accuracy Radial-velocity Planet Searcher) to detect
    previously unknown lines, perform a systematic search for blended
    lines and correct individual wavelengths by determining the systematic
    offset of each line relative to the average wavelength solution.

Description:
    This thorium and argon line list has been derived from ThAr spectra
    obtained with the HARPS instrument at the ESO-3.6m telescope at La
    Silla Observatory. It contains the updated wavelengths of 8442 lines
    between 3785 and 6915{AA}, with a typical accuracy of 10m/s (3.3 parts
    in 10^8^ or 0.18m{AA}). Line intensities, previously-known wavelengths
    and identifications are also provided.

